In its September 17 issue, Le Devoir published a letter from Mr. Patrick J. Garver, Deputy Director General of Canadian Goldmine Barrick Gold.
This confirms, and pursues, an Orwellian logic that the world’s largest gold mining company sought a defamation lawsuit of over six million against three authors and a small, mediocre publishing house, with the aim of opening a “public transparent debate.”
If it is true that the judges are independent and impartial, then they do not judge the truth, especially in the case of defamation lawsuits, but rather the law.
